OL,3,CPeston: Starmer's fate will be decided
OL,4,Cby Rayner
OL,6,FThe prime minister's survival is
OL,7,Fprobably now in the hands of his
OL,8,Fformer deputy, Angela Rayner.
OL,10,FNow that she has been absolved of
OL,11,Fwrongdoing by HMRC, his get-out-of-
OL,12,Fjail is to offer her the health job
OL,13,Fvacated by Streeting or perhaps any
OL,14,Fjob she wants.
OL,16,FShe is strong enough to dictate terms
OL,17,Fbecause she represents a large part of
OL,18,Fthe parliamentary Labour Party that
OL,19,Fwants him out. So if she throws him a
OL,20,Flifeline, they may too.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/3
