OL,3,CPeston: Starmer's fate will be decided
OL,4,Cby Rayner
OL,6,FI am imagining the conversation in
OL,7,Fwhich Rayner says to the PM that she
OL,8,Ffancies being Chancellor of the
OL,9,FExchequer and she is sure Rachel
OL,10,FReeves would excel as health secretary.
OL,12,FThis is currently all the stuff of
OL,13,Ffiction, except that whether Rayner
OL,14,Fagrees to take any job from Starmer is
OL,15,Fpotentially life or death for him.
